provincial, and municipal policing body. The RCMP provides policing services to all of Canada at a federal level, and also on a contract basis to the three territories, eight of Canada's provinces (the RCMP does not provide provincial or municipal policing in either Ontario or Quebec), more than 190 municipalities, 184 aboriginal communities, and three international airports.<\/p>","image_height":555,"geohash":"","latest_item_date":"2015-03-23T17:52:57.882278"},{"items_resource_uri":"\/api\/v1\/item\/?topics=1","related_topics_uri":"\/api\/v1\/topic\/?related_to=1","id":1,"created_on":"2012-11-28T17:18:53","recent_count":11,"image_url":"http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/4\/4b\/Pierre-Paul_Prud%27hon_-_Justice_and_Divine_Vengeance_Pursuing_Crime.JPG","permalink":"http:\/\/www.breakingnews.com\/topic\/crime-courts\/","daily_count":76,"trend_rank_last":1,"muted_by_default":false,"woeid":null,"resource_uri":"\/api\/v1\/topic\/1\/","local_url":"\/topic\/crime-courts\/","placetype":"","links":"","kind":"vertical","name":"crime & courts","category":"Topic","short_permalink":"http:\/\/www.breakingnews.com\/t\/B","wikipedia_url":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Crime","twitter_username":null,"slug":"crime-courts","facebookchat":"","image_credit":"Photo: <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Crime\">Wikipedia<\/a>","latitude":null,"active":true,"item_count":54161,"image_width":1089,"trend_rank_current":1,"longitude":null,"livevideo":"","description":"<p>In ordinary language, the term <b>crime<\/b> denotes an unlawful act punishable by a state. The term crime does not, in modern criminal law, have any simple and universally accepted definition, though statutory definitions have been provided for certain purposes. The most popular view is that crime is a category created by law (i.e. something is a crime if applicable law says that it is). One proposed definition is that a <b>crime<\/b>, also called an <b>offence<\/b> or a <b>criminal offence<\/b>, is an 