es and well-developed trade networks. Canada's long and complex relationship with the United States has had a significant impact on its economy and culture.<\/p>\n<p>Canada is a developed country and one of the wealthiest in the world, with the eighth highest per capita income globally, and the eighth highest ranking in the Human Development Index. It ranks among the highest in international measurements of education, government transparency, civil liberties, quality of life, and economic freedom. Canada also ranks among the world's most educated countries, and was ranked first worldwide in the number of adults having tertiary education with 51% of adults having attained at least an undergraduate college or university degree according to OECD's 2012 survey. Canada's participation in economic international and intergovernmental institutions or groupings includes the G8 (Group of Eight); the Group of Ten (economic); the Group of Twenty (G-20 major economies); the North American Free Trade Agreement; and the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation forum. Canada's alliances include the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).<\/p>","image_height":500,"geohash":"cf4h4bm94m8e","latest_item_date":"2015-03-23T17:52:57.882278"},{"items_resource_uri":"\/api\/v1\/item\/?topics=9674","related_topics_uri":"\/api\/v1\/topic\/?related_to=9674","id":9674,"created_on":"2010-10-05T18:51:21","recent_count":0,"image_url":"http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/c\/cc\/OttawaCollage.png","permalink":"http:\/\/www.breakingnews.com\/topic\/ottawa-ontario-ca\/","daily_count":2,"trend_rank_last":0,"muted_by_default":false,"woeid":91982014,"resource_uri":"\/api\/v1\/topic\/9674\/","local_url":"\/topic\/ottawa-ontario-ca\/","placetype":"Town","links":"","kind":"location","name":"Ottawa, Ontario, CA","category":"Town","short_permalink":"http:\/\/www.breakingnews.com\/t\/CgC","wikipedia_url":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ottawa","twitter_username":null,"slug":"ottawa-ontario-ca","fac